e young woman\nShe gave a witty, entertaining, and articulate speech.\nĐối lập\ninarticulate'),(303,'articulated',' \nAn articulated vehicle consists of two or more parts that bend where they are joined, in order to help the vehicle turn corners:\nUK An articulated lorry has overturned on the southbound carriageway, shedding its load.\nSo sánh\ntractor-trailer'),(304,'artificial',' \nB2\nmade by people, often as a copy of something natural:\nclothes made of artificial fibres\nan artificial heart\nan artificial lake\nartificial fur/sweeteners/flowers'),(305,'artist',' \nA2\nsomeone who paints, draws, or makes sculptures:\nMonet is one of my favourite artists.'),(306,'artistic',' \nB2 [ before noun ]\nrelating to art:\nthe artistic director of the theatre\nartistic endeavours\na work of artistic merit'),(307,'artwork',' \nthe pieces of art, such as drawings and photographs, that are used in books, newspapers, and magazines:\nAll the artwork in the book has been done by the author.\nTừ đồng nghĩa\ngraphics\nSo sánh\nart noun'),(308,'as',' \nA2\nused in comparisons to refer to the degree of something:\nShe\'ll soon be as tall as her mother.\nI can\'t run as fast as you.\nskin as soft as a baby\'s\nIt\'s not as good as it used to be.'),(309,'ash',' \n[ U ]\nthe soft grey or black powder that is left after a substance, especially tobacco, coal, or wood, has burned:\ncigarette ash'),(310,'ashamed',' \nB1\nfeeling guilty or embarrassed about something you have done or about a quality in your character:\nYou\'ve got nothing to be ashamed of.\nShe ought to be thoroughly ashamed of herself - talking to her mother like that!\n[   to infinitive ] He was ashamed to admit to his mistake.\n[   that ] I was ashamed that I\'d made so little effort.\nI\'m ashamed to be seen with you when you behave so badly!\nI felt so ashamed of myself for making such a fuss.\nI\'m so ashamed of you (= embarrassed to be connected with you)!\nĐối lập\nunashamed'),(311,'aside',' \nB2\non or to one side