êm\nbreadboard\nsoundboard'),(532,'boast',' \nB2 [ I or T ] disapproving\nto speak too proudly or happily about what you have done or what you own:\nHe didn\'t talk about his exam results in case people thought he was boasting.\nParents enjoy boasting about their children\'s achievements.\n[   that ] They boasted that they had never lost a single game.'),(533,'boat',' \nA1\na small vehicle for travelling on water:\na rowing/sailing boat\na fishing boat\nWe took turns to row the boat up the river.\n \nJackF/iStock/Getty Images Plus/GettyImages'),(534,'body',' \nA1 [ C ]\nthe whole physical structure that forms a person or animal:\nA good diet and plenty of exercise will help you to keep your body healthy.\nShe rubbed suncream over her entire body.'),(535,'boil',' \nA2 [ I or T ]\nto reach, or cause something to reach, the temperature at which a liquid starts to turn into a gas:\nLiquid nitrogen boils at a very low temperature.\nShe scalded herself on some boiling water.\nIf you give water to a small baby to drink, you have to boil it first.'),(536,'bold',' \nB2\nnot frightened of danger:\nShe was a bold and fearless climber.\nThe newspaper made the bold move/took the bold step of publishing the names of the men involved.\nTừ đồng nghĩa\nbrave'),(538,'bombing',' \nB2\nan attack or attacks on a place or area using bombs, or the activity of attacking in this way:\nHeavy bombing has gutted the city.\nThere was a wave of bombings in the south of the country.'),(539,'bone',' \nB1\nany of the hard parts inside a human or animal that make up its frame:\nThe child was so thin that you could see her bones.\nhuman/animal bones\n \nSCIEPRO/Science Photo Library/GettyImages'),(540,'bonus',' \nB2\nan extra amount of money that is given to you as a present or reward for good work as well as the money you were expecting:\na productivity bonus\na Christmas bonus\nThe company used to give discretionary bonus payments.'),(541,'book',' \nA1 [ C ]\na written text that can be published in