ook like some mad old woman in this hat?\nSo sánh\ninsane adjective'),(2802,'made',' \npast simple and past participle of make :\nHe was wearing a suit made from pure silk.\nThe house was made of wood with an iron roof.'),(2803,'magazine',' \nA2\n(informal mag)\na type of thin book with large pages and a paper cover that contains articles and photographs and is published every week or month:\nShe has written articles for several women\'s magazines.\na glossy magazine\nmen\'s mags\na magazine rack\n \npictafolio/E /GettyImages'),(2804,'magic',' \nA2\nthe use of special powers to make things happen that would usually be impossible, such as in stories for children:\nThe group is known for its belief in witchcraft and magic.\nAs if by magic/Like magic, the car changes into a boat when it hits the water.'),(2805,'magical',' \nB2\nproduced by or using magic:\nDiamonds were once thought to have magical powers.'),(2806,'magistrate',' \nC1\na person who acts as a judge in a law court that deals with crimes that are less serious:\nHe will appear before the magistrates tomorrow.\nGreenway appeared at Bow Street Magistrates\' Court to face seven charges of accepting bribes.'),(2807,'magnetic',' \nC1\nwith the power of a magnet'),(2808,'magnificent',' \nB1\nvery good, beautiful, or deserving to be admired:\na magnificent view\na magnificent piece of writing\nThey live in a magnificent Tudor house.\nCác từ đồng nghĩa\nbrilliant\nglorious\nsplendid formal'),(2809,'magnitude',' \nthe large size or importance of something:\nThey don\'t seem to grasp the magnitude of the problem.'),(2810,'mail',' \nA2 [ S or U ]\n(UK also post)\nthe letters, etc. that are sent to or from people, or the system for sending letters, etc. from place to place:\nShe spent the morning reading and answering her mail.\nAll of our customers will be contacted by mail.\nThe book came in yesterday\'s mail.\nSome strange things get sent through the mail.\nCác từ đồng nghĩa\ncorrespondence (WRITING)\npost (LETTERS)